From: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: as21xxx: extend firmware reset timeout to 30s

The AS21xxx cold-boot firmware initialisation takes 18-74 seconds
depending on the chip variant.  aeon_wait_reset_complete() uses
read_poll_timeout() with a 2 s ceiling, so on a cold power-on the
first config_init() call always times out, falls through to
aeon_firmware_load(), and the second 2 s wait times out as well,
returning -ENODEV.

The PHY state machine then retries config_init() only on a link
event (cable pull/re-insert), which is why the port appears dead
after reboot until the cable is cycled.

Raise the ceiling to 30 s so the cold-start firmware boot (typically
~18 s) completes within the first wait_reset_complete() call.  Warm
resets where firmware is already running respond immediately, so
there is no practical latency increase for that case.

Signed-off-by: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/as21xxx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/phy/as21xxx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/as21xxx.c
@@ -1512,7 +1512,7 @@ static int aeon_wait_reset_complete(stru
 	int val;

 	return read_poll_timeout(aeon_ipc_get_fw_version, val,
-				 val == 0, 10000, 2000000, false, phydev);
+				 val == 0, 10000, 30000000, false, phydev);
 }

 static int aeon_gen1_config_init(struct phy_device *phydev)
